HEADWORD: Burier
<hw>Bur"i*er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who, or that
which, buries.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Till the <qex>buriers</qex> have buried it.</q> <rj><qau>Ezek.
xxxix. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And darkness be the <qex>burier</qex> of the dead.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

